SUMMARY:How NASA Sends Science Into Space
DESCRIPTION:NASA’s Launch Services Program is coming to the North Carolina Museum of Natural Sciences on April 8\, 2026\, at 1:30 PM\nJoin us for an engaging presentation exploring how NASA sends science and robotic missions into space. Discover the rockets that power these missions\, learn about NASA career pathways\, and hear stories from behind the scenes at Kennedy Space Center. \nVisitors will have the opportunity to ask questions\, dive deeper into NASA’s work\, and take home exciting NASA outreach materials. It’s a great event for space enthusiasts of all ages—don’t miss it! \nToday’s Expert \nJarrod Bales\, NASA\, Education and Outreach Specialist
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/launching-wonder-how-nasa-sends-science-into-space/
LOCATION:Nature Research Center\, 121 West Jones Street\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27601\, United States
CATEGORIES:All Ages,General Events,K-12 Students,Lectures,Meet the Scientist,SECU Daily Planet Theater,Walk-up Programs
ORGANIZER;CN="Chris%20Smith":MAILTO:christopher.smith@naturalsciences.org
