SUMMARY:Lifelong Hike: Howell Woods Birding
DESCRIPTION:Birds will be our focus on this special birding experience at Howell Woods. Located in southeastern Johnston County\, Howell Woods is a 2800-acre natural area owned and managed by Johnston Community College for educational and recreational purposes. After an indoor introductory session\, Howell Woods staff and guest biologists will lead our exploration of some of the diverse habitats in search of birds. \nPlease note: You will be required to enter the following information for each registrant before you can complete your registration: emergency contact\, physician contact and health information (allergies\, conditions\, medications relevant to this field experience). Take a moment to gather this information before beginning your registration. \nREGISTRATION FOR THIS TRIP IS FULL \nIf the trip is full\, please email Missy Chernick to be added to the waitlist. \nRegistration deadline: Monday\, April 13 at 8:00 AM \nFor additional information about this trip and other Lifelong Hikes & Adventures\, contact Jerry Reynolds at 919.707.9884.
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/lifelong-hike-howell-woods-birding/
LOCATION:In the Field
CATEGORIES:Adults,Lifelong Learners,Outdoor Experiences,Trips
END:VEVENT
