SUMMARY:Lunchtime Discovery: Conservation Corps 101: Connecting Young People to Service in North Carolina
DESCRIPTION:Join us in-person in the SECU Daily Planet Theater or watch the livestream on YouTube. \nFrom the original Civilian Conservation Corps to today’s modern movement\, join us to learn how conservation corps programs connect the dots between conservation action and workforce development. Hear how Conservation Corps North Carolina is creating unique experiences for youth and young adults around the state to work and serve while building skills in land management\, forestry\, disaster recovery\, species conservation\, parks and recreation management\, GIS\, and so much more. \nJessie Birckhead\, Executive Director\, Conservation Corps North Carolina \n\nThroughout the month of April\, the Lunchtime Discovery Series will recognize Earth Day. These live presentations will be held Wednesdays from noon to 1:00 p.m. and are hosted by the NC Museum of Natural Sciences Coordinator of Current Science Programs Chris Smith. \nBrought to you by the NC DEQ Office of Environmental Education and Public Affairs and the NC Museum of Natural Sciences.
URL:https://naturalsciences.org/calendar/event/lunchtime-discovery-conservation-corps-101-connecting-young-people-to-service-in-north-carolina/
LOCATION:Nature Research Center\, 121 West Jones Street\, Raleigh\, NC\, 27601\, United States
CATEGORIES:Adults,Discussions,Educators,General Events,K-12 Students,Lectures,Lunchtime Discovery,Teens,Virtual
ORGANIZER;CN="Chris%20Smith":MAILTO:christopher.smith@naturalsciences.org
